author: Tatyana Shumsky
title: Gold Near Flat As Traders Weigh Weaker Dollar, Likely Fed Rate Path
text:
Gold prices paced on either side of unchanged Tuesday as investors weighed support from a weaker dollar against the likelihood that the Federal Reserve will soon raise interest rates.
The most actively traded contract, for December delivery, was recently down $1, or 0.1%, at $1,120.40 a troy ounce on the Comex division of the New York Mercantile Exchange.
